  "texts": [
    "In terms of software, our framework implementation uses Unity Editor version 2019.4.29f1 with the OpenVR desktop and SteamVR runtime.",
    "To support spatial manipulation of a NeRF model in VR, we create a model space for the NeRF model whose spatial properties such as position, rotation, and scale are defined by a volume bounding box.",
    "As Figures 2A, B shows, the bounding box is represented as a transparent cube whose translation, rotation, and scale matrices are combined into one transformation matrix that is applied to the view matrix of the instant-ngp camera to render the correct view of the NeRF model.",
    "The model-view-projection (VPM) matrix is applied to instant-ngp renderer through the native CUDA and C++ plugin.",
    "The object manipulation interaction from the Mixed Reality Toolkit (MRTK) foot_4 is attached to the cube, allowing users to intuitively rotate, scale, and translate the box and its associated NeRF model using one-or twohanded control."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}